### HTML lists
- *Odered Lists*: list where each item in the list is numbered.
- **Unordered Lists: list that began with a bullet point.
- Definition lists: made up of a set of items along with definitions for each of these items.
1. There are 3 types of html lists
2. List can be nested inside one another.

 Links are the defining feature of the web b/c they allow you to move from one web page to another.
 Links are created using the <a> element.
 When you link to another website, the value of the *href* attribute will be the full web address of the site.
 
 ##BOXES
 . Controlling the size of boxes
